      <category><![CDATA[organic]]></category>
      <category><![CDATA[organic cotton]]></category>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">http://spiffybaby.com/resources/?p=308</guid>
      <description>Why Organic? Cotton is the world&amp;#8217;s most popular fabric. Soft and comfortable, it&amp;#8217;s used for almost every type of clothing. Organically raised cotton is gradually winning over new ground in the marketplace. No toxins or synthetic fertilizers are used. Organic cotton is produced without the use of harsh chemical bleaches or dyes, and is allergy [...]&lt;br&gt;&lt;a type="audio/mpeg" href="http://podcasts.odiogo.com/get_mp3.mp3?f=/spiffy-baby-talk-a-place-where-one-savvy-parent-m/Spiffy_Baby_Talk_-_a_place_where_one_savvy_parent_-Organic_and_bamboo_cotton_clothing.mp3"&gt;Click here to play&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;</description>
      <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><img class="alignleft" style="float: left;" src="http://www.spiffybaby.com/images/t_806_01.jpg" alt="" width="280" height="340" />Why Organic? Cotton is the world&#8217;s most popular fabric. Soft and comfortable, it&#8217;s used for almost every type of clothing. Organically raised cotton is gradually winning over new ground in the marketplace. No toxins or synthetic fertilizers are used. <span style="font-weight: normal;">Organic cotton </span>is produced without the use of harsh chemical bleaches or dyes, and is allergy free. New methods of coloring cotton are also being developed to address the problem of toxic dyes- organically colored cotton. Earth tones are now available which use no dyes whatsoever.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.spiffybaby.com/Organic-Cotton-Clothing-p-1-c-186.html"></a>Bamboo fiber has been publicized as THE natural, green,&lt;!&#8211;adsense#postad&#8211;&gt; renewable and eco-friendly textile of the 21st Century. Bamboo thrives naturally without the use of pesticides, and is 100% biodegradable in soil by micro-organism and sunshine, causing no pollution to the environment. Bamboo naturally exhibits these characteristics: anti-bacterial; anti-fungal; anti-static; natural antibiosis qualities keep bacterium in check, decreasing bad odors; micro-gaps in the bamboo fiber give a <span style="font-weight: bold;"><span style="font-weight: normal;">moisture</span> <span style="font-weight: normal;">absorption</span></span> rate 3X that of regular cotton; ultra-plush texture is soft on sensitive skin.<br />
Organic and bamboo cotton clothing is now available for babies and parents at SpiffyBaby.com from premier brands and designers. Hard to find organic cotton items, such as organic denim, and even organic socks, are easily available in our online boutique.</p>
<div class="awmp_tags"><a href="http://spiffybaby.com/resources/search/organic/" rel="tag">organic</a> <a href="http://spiffybaby.com/resources/search/cotton/" rel="tag">cotton</a> <a href="http://spiffybaby.com/resources/search/bamboo fiber/" rel="tag">bamboo fiber</a> <a href="http://spiffybaby.com/resources/search/eco-friendly/" rel="tag">eco-friendly</a> <a href="http://spiffybaby.com/resources/search/biodegradable/" rel="tag">biodegradable</a> <a href="http://spiffybaby.com/resources/search/organic cotton/" rel="tag">organic cotton</a> <a href="http://spiffybaby.com/resources/search/baby clothes/" rel="tag">baby clothes</a></div>]]></content:encoded>
      <wfw:commentRss>http://spiffybaby.com/resources/2010/03/16/organic-and-bamboo-cotton-clothing/feed</wfw:commentRss>
